Set optional complex property to null, does not set inner properties value-type with default value inner properties to null

### Bug description

Related to  but opposite direction.

When an entity has an optional complex property, and that complex property contains a non‑nullable value‑type property whose value is the default, setting the complex property from a non‑null instance to null is not fully detected by the change tracker. As a result, inner value‑type properties that are at their default values are ignored and are not updated to NULL in the database.

If the non‑nullable value‑type property is set to any value other than its default, the change tracker correctly identifies the change and updates the corresponding database column to NULL.
A current workaround is to make the inner value‑type properties nullable.


